   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_1841_02_22_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline><!--If there's no date line, remove this element. Record in the order in which it is written on the letter.-->
                  <placeName ref="Id_where"/>
                  <date when="1111-11-11">Month DD, YYYY</date></dateline>
               <salute>
                  <persName>
                     <!-- Use if letter has a saluation ("Dear Sir," for example). If not, delete this line.-->
                  </persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>1 North Audley Street<lb/>
               Feb<hi rend= "superscript">y</hi> 22<hi rend= "superscript">d</hi> 1841<lb/>
               Dear Sir<lb/>
               Your offer of 50 guineas, guineas, at six<lb/>
               months date after publication<lb/>
               for the copy right of a translation<lb/>
               by my sister Lucy E from the<lb/>
               French of the three stories of<lb/>
               Barnabe - Pierre &amp; Pierrette<lb/>
               and Marguerite, with a<lb/>
               preface, and explanatory<lb/>
               remarks for young English<lb/>
               readers to be written by me<lb/>
               I accept for my sister and<lb/>
               myself and consider as<lb/>
               liberal<lb/>
               I am <hi rend= "underline">D<hi rend= "superscript">r</hi> Sir</hi> with the belief<lb/>
               that the putting this our little<lb/>
               agreement thus carefully in<lb/>
               writing, trifling though it<lb/>
               be compared with your<lb/>
               great affairs, is the way to<lb/>
               ensure our being as well<lb/>
               pleased with each other<lb/>
               at the end as we are at<lb/>
               this beginning of our connexion<lb/>
               as publishers &amp; authors<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
              Yours sincerely<lb/>
                  Maria Edgeworth<lb/></closer>
            <closer>
               <address>
                  <addrLine>To</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>John Murray Esq<hi rend= "superscript">re</hi></addrLine>
               </address>
            </closer>
         </div>
